com.adobe.aemforms.fm.model

Class FormsetItem

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.adobe.aemforms.fm.model.FormsetItem

  • public class FormsetItem
extends Object
    FormsetItem contains the information about a Form in the Form Set. A List of FormsetItem is stored in FormsetOptions while passing to FormGenerationService to create Form Set.

        public void setFormPath(String formPath)
        sets the full repository path(with name) of the Form. This is mandatory field to specify. If null or empty, Form Set creation FAILS.
        Parameters:
        formPath - representing full repository path(with name) where this Form exists.

      • getFormIdentifier

      • setFormIdentifier

        public void setFormIdentifier(String formIdentifier)
        sets the identifier of the Form. This property is used to uniquely identify the Form in an eligibility expression. If null or empty, this is auto generated using the name of the Form. If 2 Forms have same name in the Form Set, auto-generation FAILS and thus, Form Set creation FAILS. If Form identifier of 2 Forms is same in the Form Set, Form Set creation FAILS.
        Parameters:
        formIdentifier -

      • getEligibiltyExpression

        public String getEligibiltyExpression()
        returns eligibility expression of the Form.
        Returns:
        String representing eligibility expression of the Form.

      • setEligibiltyExpression

        public void setEligibiltyExpression(String eligibiltyExpression)
        sets eligibility expression of the Form. Eligibility expressions in a Form Set are used to define and dynamically control Forms that are displayed to a user. An eligibility expression can be any valid JavaScript statement that returns a Boolean value. If the value of the expression is true, the Form is eligible to be displayed to the user. Eligibility expression for the first Form in Form Set is not executed. The first form is always displayed regardless of its eligibility expression.
        Parameters:
        eligibiltyExpression -
